Show HN: Scut – Shortcuts in the Windows CLI
text:
scut is a little tool that gives you basic directory aliasing functionality on the windows command line. You can open a directory in explorer or cd into it.

To use, drop scut.bat into a directory that is on your path.

scut stores your shortcuts in a flat file located %HOMEDRIVE%%HOMEPATH%\AppData\Roaming\scut-db.txt

https://github.com/ShamariFeaster/scut
